aa(lp33
VNow, in one sense,
p34
aVthe claim that history has a direction is not that controversial.
p35
aVIf you're just talking about social structure,
p36
aVOK, clearly that's gotten more complex
p37
aVa little over the last 10,000 years \u2014 has reached higher and higher levels.
p38
aVAnd in fact, that's actually sustaining
p39
aVa long-standing trend that predates human beings, OK,
p40
aVthat biological evolution was doing for us.
p41
aVBecause what happened in the beginning, this stuff encases itself in a cell,
p42
aVthen cells start hanging out together in societies.
p43
aVEventually they get so close, they form multicellular organisms,
p44
aVthen you get complex multicellular organisms; they form societies.
p45
aa(lp46
VBut then at some point, one of these multicellular organisms
p47
aVdoes something completely amazing with this stuff, which is
p48
aVit launches a whole second kind of evolution: cultural evolution.
p49
aVAnd amazingly, that evolution sustains the trajectory
p50
aVthat biological evolution had established toward greater complexity.
p51
aVBy cultural evolution we mean the evolution of ideas.
p52
aVA lot of you have heard the term "memes." The evolution of technology,
p53
aVI pay a lot of attention to, so, you know,
p54
aVone of the first things you got was a little hand axe.
p55
aVGenerations go by, somebody says, hey, why don't we put it on a stick?
p56
aV(Laughter)
p57
aVJust absolutely delights the little ones.
p58
aVNext best thing to a video game.
p59
aa(lp60
VThis may not seem to impress,
p61
aVbut technological evolution is progressive, so another 10, 20,000 years,
p62
aVand armaments technology takes you here.
p63
aV(Laughter)
p64
aVImpressive. And the rate of technological evolution speeds up,
p65
aVso a mere quarter of a century after this, you get this, OK.
p66
aV(Laughter)
p67
aVAnd this.
p68
aV(Laughter)
p69
aVI'm sorry \u2014 it was a cheap laugh, but I wanted to find a way
